A pleasant area in which to live or work, comprising the village of Souldrop and surrounding farmland. The local people believe it is a{healthy place to live, as expressed in the saying: 'Souldrop air and Sharnbrook water, make a man live here and hereafter.'
The area has been greatly affected over the years by its proximity to Colworth House, a former{stately home and now a major food research establishment.
As soon as you get away from the main Rushden to Bedford road the tranquilty of the area is broken only by the occasional rumble of passing{trains and less frequently by low flying aircraft.}
